8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 633, L.D. 1549, “RESOLUTION,
10 Proposing an Amendment to the Constitution of Maine Regarding the Use and Oversight
11 of Transportation-related Revenues”
12 Amend the resolution in that part designated "Constitution, Art. IX, §19" in §19 by
13 inserting after the first blocked paragraph the following:
14 'Beginning July 1, 2028 and annually thereafter, an additional 5% of the sales and use tax
15 revenue collected from motor vehicle dealers and by a state department having jurisdiction
16 over motor vehicles must be transferred to the Highway Fund or successor fund until 100%
17 of the sales and use tax revenue collected from motor vehicle dealers and by the state
18 department having jurisdiction over motor vehicles is transferred to the Highway Fund or
19 successor fund.'
20 Amend the resolution in the question in the last line (page 1, line 39 in L.D.) by
21 inserting after the following: "Fund" the following: ', with an annual increase of at least 5%
22 until 100% of the sales and use tax revenue collected from motor vehicle dealers and the
23 Bureau of Motor Vehicles is transferred'
24 Amend the resolution by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or
25 section number to read consecutively.
26 SUMMARY
2277 This amendment, which is the minority report of the committee, proposes to further
2288 amend the Constitution of Maine by adding that, beginning July 1, 2028 and annually
2299 thereafter, an additional 5% of the sales and use tax revenue collected from motor vehicle
3300 dealers and by the state department having jurisdiction over motor vehicles must be
3311 transferred to the Highway Fund or successor fund until 100% of the sales and use tax
3322 revenue collected from motor vehicle dealers and by the state department having
3333 jurisdiction over motor vehicles is transferred to the Highway Fund or successor fund.
